        <main class="blog-container">
            <h1 class="blog-title">Mastering Markdown: How to Implement It in Your Blog</h1>
            <p class="blog-meta">Published on February 14, 2025 by Devios</p>
            
            <section class="blog-content">
                <h2 id="what-is-markdown">What is Markdown?</h2>
                <p>Markdown is a lightweight markup language used to format text using simple syntax. It is commonly used for writing blog posts, documentation, and even README files on GitHub.</p>
                
                <h2 id="why-use-markdown">Why Use Markdown?</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Easy to write and read.</li>
                    <li>Converts into clean HTML automatically.</li>
                    <li>Lightweight and efficient for blogging.</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h2 id="steps-to-implement">Steps to Implement Markdown in Your Blog</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Include the <code>marked.js</code> library:</li>
                    <pre><code>&lt;script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/marked/marked.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
                    <li>Create a textarea for user input:</li>
                    <pre><code>&lt;textarea id="markdown-input" placeholder="Write your Markdown here..."&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;</code></pre>
                    <li>Create a preview div:</li>
                    <pre><code>&lt;div id="preview"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
                    <li>Use JavaScript to convert Markdown to HTML:</li>
                    <pre><code>document.getElementById("markdown-input").addEventListener("input", function() {
    document.getElementById("preview").innerHTML = marked.parse(this.value);
});</code></pre>
                </ol>
            </section>
            
